3x latency increases\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"component\": \"redis\",\n      \"reason\": \"rrt_max\",\n      \"evidence\": \"Redis operations (HMSET/HGET) experienced massive latency spikes from normal 1.3-1.7s to 20.8-76.7s, indicating Redis performance degradation affecting cartservice\"\n    }\n  ]\n}\n```\n\n## Root Cause Analysis\n\nThe abnormal event was primarily caused by **Redis performance degradation** that cascaded through the system:\n\n1. **Primary Root Cause**: Redis database operations (HMSET/HGET) experienced extreme latency increases (15-43x), severely impacting cartservice operations.\n\n2. **Cascade Effect**: \n   - Cartservice became unresponsive due to Redis dependency\n   - Checkoutservice was heavily affected as it relies on cartservice for cart operations\n   - Frontend services experienced delays due to checkoutservice bottlenecks\n\n3. **Key Evidence**:\n   - Cartservice GetCart latency increased from 2.3s to 77.9s (34x)\n   - Redis operations spiked from 1.3-1.7s to 20.8-76.7s\n   - Checkout PlaceOrder latency increased from 154.7s to 276.4s\n\nThe Redis performance degradation appears to be the initial failure point that propagated through the cartservice and checkoutservice dependencies, causing the overall system anomaly.", "metric_analysis_findings": "Based on the metric analysis, I can identify several key anomalies during the specified time period. Let me analyze the root cause by examining the most significant metric changes.\n\n```json\n{\n  \"stance\": \"SUPPORT\",\n  \"detected_metric_keys\": [\"node_memory_usage_rate\", \"node_memory_MemAvailable_bytes\", \"rrt_max\", \"rrt\", \"memory_usage\", \"error_ratio\"],\n  \"hypotheses\": [\n    {\n      \"component\": \"aiops-k8s-05\",\n      \"reason\": \"Node memory usage rate dropped significantly by 51.49% (from 32.62% to 19.26%) while available memory increased by 18.24%, indicating potential memory pressure or resource reallocation issues affecting service performance\",\n      \"evidence\": \"node_memory_usage_rate decreased from 32.62% to 19.26% (51.49% change), node_memory_MemAvailable_bytes increased from 11.17GB to 13.41GB\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"component\": \"cartservice-1\",\n      \"reason\": \"Significant latency degradation with rrt_max increasing by 156.75% and rrt by 139.64%, indicating performance issues in this specific pod\",\n      \"evidence\": \"rrt_max increased from 3246ms to 79619ms (156.75% p99 change), rrt increased from 1550.76ms to 12427.59ms (139.64% p99 change)\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"component\": \"tidb-tidb\",\n      \"reason\": \"Memory usage increased by 11.64% during the fault period, potentially indicating database memory pressure affecting overall system performance\",\n      \"evidence\": \"memory_usage increased from 774.85MB to 870.65MB (11.64% median change)\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"component\": \"aiops-k8s-08\",\n      \"reason\": \"Available memory decreased by 21.07% on this node, which hosts critical services including redis-cart-0 and frontend-2, potentially causing resource contention\",\n      \"evidence\": \"node_memory_MemAvailable_bytes decreased from 10.38GB to 8.41GB (21.07% median change)\"\n    }\n  ]\n}\n```\n\n**Key Analysis Points:**\n\n1. **Primary Issue**: Node aiops-k8s-05 shows the most dramatic memory behavior change with a 51.49% drop in memory usage rate, which is unusual and suggests potential memory management issues or resource reallocation problems.\n\n2. **Service Impact**: cartservice-1 shows severe latency degradation (156.75% increase in rrt_max), making it the most affected service pod.\n\n3. **Database Pressure**: TiDB memory usage increased by 11.64%, indicating potential database-level resource pressure.\n\n4. **Memory Contention**: aiops-k8s-08 experienced significant available memory reduction (21.07%), affecting critical services like redis-cart-0 and frontend-2.\n\nThe root cause appears to be a combination of node-level memory management issues on aiops-k8s-05 and aiops-k8s-08, which cascaded into service performance degradation, particularly affecting cartservice-1 and the TiDB database."}
